WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.937 --> 00:00:08.506
Family lore has it
when he topped Johnson Mesa


2
00:00:08.639 --> 00:00:10.407
and he looked down
at this valley


3
00:00:10.541 --> 00:00:15.378
and saw buffalo and antelope
belly deep in a sea of grass,


4
00:00:15.513 --> 00:00:17.782
with the Sangre de Christos
behind him,


5
00:00:17.915 --> 00:00:19.484
he knew this was it.

6
00:00:20.350 --> 00:00:22.620
Your people have
been here ever since.


7
00:00:32.463 --> 00:00:35.666
Now me, I was born
in Louisiana,


8
00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:37.635
came out here after the war.

9
00:00:38.503 --> 00:00:42.072
I was a wandering soul,
looking for a North Star.


10
00:00:43.708 --> 00:00:47.578
And I found it right here in
this valley along this river.


11
00:00:52.015 --> 00:00:54.084
To me, this is
the Peace River.


12
00:00:55.620 --> 00:00:58.556
I feel peace
every time I look at it.


13
00:00:58.689 --> 00:01:01.358
Casey, what you want to
be when you grow up?


14
00:01:02.460 --> 00:01:05.161
A cowboy,
just like you, Pop.


15
00:01:08.966 --> 00:01:12.068
[Bo] Well, you come from
a long line of cowboys.


16
00:01:12.202 --> 00:01:15.740
The cowboy loves big
sky and open range.


17
00:01:16.574 --> 00:01:20.210
Works hard,
is a man of his word.


18
00:01:21.077 --> 00:01:23.079
Loyal to his friends
and family.


19
00:01:23.881 --> 00:01:27.150
Treats everyone with respect,
especially women.


20
00:01:30.420 --> 00:01:33.524
Is courageous,
fearing God and no man.


21
00:01:36.059 --> 00:01:38.496
Don't ever forget
what's important.


22
00:01:38.629 --> 00:01:42.633
Friendship with God.
Family. Friends.


23
00:01:43.768 --> 00:01:48.238
Meaningful work
and one good horse.


24
00:01:52.777 --> 00:01:56.047
Never make the mistake
of measuring wealth by money.


25
00:01:56.179 --> 00:01:57.448
You do that,

26
00:01:57.582 --> 00:02:00.685
and you'll be a rich man
and a good cowboy.


27
00:02:02.319 --> 00:02:03.854
That's what I want to be.

28
00:02:05.255 --> 00:02:07.390
♪♪

29
00:02:12.897 --> 00:02:15.566
[Man] I met your grandmother
on the spring round-up.


30
00:02:16.333 --> 00:02:19.369
I loved her from
the first time I saw her.


31
00:02:19.503 --> 00:02:22.640
The love of a good woman
can save your life.


32
00:02:24.442 --> 00:02:25.843
When I came back
from the war,


33
00:02:25.977 --> 00:02:29.480
I had shrapnel in places
the doctors couldn't get to.


34
00:02:30.581 --> 00:02:32.182
The doctor said
I better live well


35
00:02:32.315 --> 00:02:34.752
because I probably
wouldn't live long.


36
00:02:35.686 --> 00:02:38.188
Son, that was 40 years ago,

37
00:02:38.321 --> 00:02:40.156
and I ain't dead yet.

38
00:02:42.425 --> 00:02:43.961
Be thankful.

39
00:02:44.095 --> 00:02:46.697
Always be thankful.

40
00:02:53.571 --> 00:02:55.773
All right.
No peeking. No peeking.


41
00:03:00.011 --> 00:03:01.445
All right.
You ready?


42
00:03:01.579 --> 00:03:02.613
Yes, sir.

43
00:03:05.983 --> 00:03:07.885
Well, what do you think?

44
00:03:08.019 --> 00:03:09.620
He's beautiful.

45
00:03:10.521 --> 00:03:12.757
Well, you know,
at the end of the day,


46
00:03:12.890 --> 00:03:14.257
cowboyin' is teamwork.

47
00:03:14.391 --> 00:03:17.193
Cowboy is only as good
as his horse.


48
00:03:17.327 --> 00:03:19.362
So I've been looking for
your one for a while.


49
00:03:19.497 --> 00:03:21.532
I think this may
be the one.


50
00:03:22.399 --> 00:03:25.770
Now, listen, he got
a lot of cow in him,


51
00:03:25.903 --> 00:03:27.972
so don't you be trying
to teach him anything.


52
00:03:28.105 --> 00:03:31.008
If you pay attention,
he'll teach you something.


53
00:03:31.142 --> 00:03:32.308
Okay?

54
00:03:32.443 --> 00:03:34.411
All right.
Go see what you think.


55
00:03:46.490 --> 00:03:48.726
His name is Pecos.

56
00:03:56.033 --> 00:03:58.903
Hey, Pecos.
I'm Casey.


57
00:04:00.771 --> 00:04:02.873
And I'm gonna take
good care of you.


58
00:04:04.475 --> 00:04:07.978
[chattering in Spanish]

59
00:04:08.112 --> 00:04:09.980
Casey, slow it down, buddy.

60
00:04:10.114 --> 00:04:11.549
Okay, that's it.

61
00:04:23.461 --> 00:04:25.763
Hey, you kids
stick together.


62
00:04:25.896 --> 00:04:27.698
No running!

63
00:04:29.500 --> 00:04:31.334
Those kids were born running.

64
00:04:39.443 --> 00:04:41.212
That'll be two bits.

65
00:04:41.344 --> 00:04:44.014
Drop it in
Bo's jar on the way out.


66
00:04:44.148 --> 00:04:46.249
Little Casey
had a head start.


67
00:04:46.382 --> 00:04:47.885
Two bits all the same.

68
00:04:49.419 --> 00:04:50.921
[bells rings]

69
00:04:52.123 --> 00:04:54.225
- Hey, Casey.
- Oh, no.


70
00:04:55.291 --> 00:04:58.229
I guess you Shanes will take
in any strays, even beaners.


71
00:04:58.361 --> 00:04:59.663
You are so stupid.

72
00:04:59.797 --> 00:05:02.500
That's funny,
coming from a fence jumper.


73
00:05:05.069 --> 00:05:06.436
[grunts]

74
00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:08.572
[bell rings]

75
00:05:08.706 --> 00:05:11.407
Mr. Shane, I appreciate
you coming in today.


76
00:05:11.542 --> 00:05:13.878
Yesterday on the playground,
there was an altercation


77
00:05:14.011 --> 00:05:15.278
with your grandson.

78
00:05:15.411 --> 00:05:18.649
We have a zero tolerance
policy for fighting.


79
00:05:18.783 --> 00:05:20.951
He needs to be suspended
for a day.


80
00:05:21.719 --> 00:05:23.821
I don't understand.

81
00:05:23.954 --> 00:05:25.456
What did I do wrong?

82
00:05:26.457 --> 00:05:28.859
Well, Case,
you had good intentions


83
00:05:28.993 --> 00:05:31.695
of defending Maria's
dignity and honor.


84
00:05:32.630 --> 00:05:35.365
But the problem is,
you delivered the first blow.


85
00:05:36.600 --> 00:05:38.135
There's only two blows
a cowboy


86
00:05:38.269 --> 00:05:39.837
ought to deliver for sure.

87
00:05:39.970 --> 00:05:42.673
That's the second one
and the last one.


88
00:05:44.475 --> 00:05:45.776
You know,
if everybody responded


89
00:05:45.910 --> 00:05:48.746
to every verbal provocation
in this world,


90
00:05:49.613 --> 00:05:51.816
civilization
would come unglued.


91
00:06:04.327 --> 00:06:05.629
You okay?

92
00:06:05.763 --> 00:06:09.600
Grandma, you reckon
he's still mad at me?


93
00:06:09.733 --> 00:06:12.703
Heck, no,
he ain't mad at you.


94
00:06:14.071 --> 00:06:16.841
Casey, that man loves you
more than you can know.


95
00:06:19.076 --> 00:06:22.713
He just wants you to be
a kind and a strong man.


96
00:06:27.284 --> 00:06:29.787
♪♪

97
00:07:05.356 --> 00:07:07.423
Hey, little buddy.

98
00:07:07.558 --> 00:07:09.460
What you looking at there?

99
00:07:17.334 --> 00:07:19.169
What was my daddy like?

100
00:07:20.237 --> 00:07:22.840
Man, your daddy
was something else.


101
00:07:23.707 --> 00:07:25.776
Full of life and laughter.

102
00:07:26.543 --> 00:07:28.279
As the cowboys would say,
he was a man


103
00:07:28.411 --> 00:07:29.914
to ride the river with.

104
00:07:31.248 --> 00:07:32.683
What a cowboy.

105
00:07:33.884 --> 00:07:36.820
That boy could ride
the hair off a bull.


106
00:07:37.855 --> 00:07:41.492
And you know,
when I look at you,


107
00:07:42.459 --> 00:07:45.562
I often think
I'm looking at him.


108
00:07:49.500 --> 00:07:51.936
Why did God let my daddy die?

109
00:07:55.172 --> 00:07:58.542
Case, there are some things
in this life that


110
00:07:58.676 --> 00:08:01.445
it's hard
to understand or explain.


111
00:08:02.813 --> 00:08:04.148
We just have to...

112
00:08:05.382 --> 00:08:06.951
trust in God.

113
00:08:07.851 --> 00:08:12.122
I believe God is, and he's good
in all that he does.


114
00:08:12.923 --> 00:08:14.758
I believe there's a heaven.

115
00:08:16.527 --> 00:08:18.629
And someday you
and me and Grandma


116
00:08:18.762 --> 00:08:21.565
and your mom will be
with your dad in heaven.


117
00:08:24.134 --> 00:08:26.270
So, Lord,
I thank You for Casey.


118
00:08:27.271 --> 00:08:30.240
I pray that You give him
the dreams of God tonight.


119
00:08:31.976 --> 00:08:33.544
We thank You
for our loved ones


120
00:08:33.677 --> 00:08:35.646
