01:05:16.279 --> 01:05:17.981
[speaking foreign language]

1000
01:05:22.319 --> 01:05:24.054
This is General Daood.

1001
01:05:24.856 --> 01:05:26.657
[speaking foreign language]

1002
01:05:26.791 --> 01:05:28.024
Please.

1003
01:05:29.926 --> 01:05:31.496
Joe, Tu, take watch out front.

1004
01:05:40.370 --> 01:05:42.372
[speaking foreign language]

1005
01:05:51.081 --> 01:05:52.817
We are very grateful
you are here.


1006
01:05:53.618 --> 01:05:56.854
More Americans come
when the towers fall.


1007
01:05:56.987 --> 01:05:59.256
We prevail,
we're very thankful.


1008
01:05:59.389 --> 01:06:01.358
[speaking foreign language]

1009
01:06:06.697 --> 01:06:09.232
The Taliban have ruined
our country.


1010
01:06:09.366 --> 01:06:11.935
Our men are very valiant.

1011
01:06:12.068 --> 01:06:13.838
We will fight the ground.

1012
01:06:13.970 --> 01:06:15.939
We need your air support.

1013
01:06:16.072 --> 01:06:17.608
[speaking foreign language]

1014
01:06:18.876 --> 01:06:20.645
Do your men ride horses?

1015
01:06:25.883 --> 01:06:27.350
All experts, sir.

1016
01:06:51.776 --> 01:06:53.243
[speaking foreign language]

1017
01:06:58.081 --> 01:06:59.550
Cars cannot
climb mountains.


1018
01:06:59.684 --> 01:07:03.987
Elevation.
It is key in my country,


1019
01:07:04.120 --> 01:07:07.725
mobility for battle
effectiveness.


1020
01:07:10.227 --> 01:07:12.162
[speaking foreign language]

1021
01:07:15.198 --> 01:07:17.000
Huddle up on me.

1022
01:07:27.410 --> 01:07:30.013
Our Father, who art in heaven,

1023
01:07:30.146 --> 01:07:31.449
hallowed by thy name.

1024
01:07:31.582 --> 01:07:33.951
Thy kingdom come,
thy will be done


1025
01:07:34.084 --> 01:07:36.253
on Earth as it
is in heaven.


1026
01:07:36.386 --> 01:07:38.421
Give us this day
our daily bread


1027
01:07:38.556 --> 01:07:40.658
and forgive us our trespasses,

1028
01:07:40.791 --> 01:07:43.494
as we forgive those
who trespass against us.


1029
01:07:43.628 --> 01:07:46.831
Lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil.


1030
01:07:46.964 --> 01:07:48.566
Blessed be the Lord.

1031
01:07:48.699 --> 01:07:52.837
My God, my rock, who prepareth
my hands for war,


1032
01:07:52.970 --> 01:07:54.539
and my fingers for battle.

1033
01:07:55.338 --> 01:07:57.374
Lord have mercy
on every soul...


1034
01:07:58.843 --> 01:08:00.343
we're about to send to you.

1035
01:08:04.247 --> 01:08:06.751
♪♪

1036
01:08:36.013 --> 01:08:37.848
Hey, they look like they're
about to make a cavalry charge.


1037
01:08:37.982 --> 01:08:39.016
They say anything about that?

1038
01:08:39.149 --> 01:08:40.685
Negative.
Not that I heard.


1039
01:08:40.818 --> 01:08:42.352
Mm-mm.

1040
01:08:42.486 --> 01:08:45.489
21st century cavalry charge,
Bo ain't gonna believe this.


1041
01:08:48.425 --> 01:08:50.393
Hey, I ain't missing
this, fellas.


1042
01:08:51.294 --> 01:08:52.697
You're not going without me.

1043
01:08:52.830 --> 01:08:54.065
Well, come on, brother.
What do you say, Chief?


1044
01:08:54.197 --> 01:08:56.399
Time to go kinetic.

1045
01:08:56.534 --> 01:08:58.803
Hey, guys, me and Tu
will stay behind,


1046
01:08:58.936 --> 01:09:00.337
calling in our CAS.

1047
01:09:00.471 --> 01:09:01.872
We'll rendezvous from here

1048
01:09:02.006 --> 01:09:03.239
straight down the wadi.

1049
01:09:03.373 --> 01:09:05.543
Nobody goes through the pass.
Nobody.


1050
01:09:07.478 --> 01:09:11.114
Guys, drop everything
but your arms and ammo.


1051
01:09:18.089 --> 01:09:20.390
- Let's do this.
- [All] Hoi!


1052
01:09:35.806 --> 01:09:37.440
[gunfire]

1053
01:09:43.279 --> 01:09:44.515
Ah!

1054
01:09:55.826 --> 01:09:57.427
[gunfire continues]

1055
01:10:07.370 --> 01:10:08.939
Many Muslims say...

1056
01:10:11.575 --> 01:10:13.944
Americans are infidels.

1057
01:10:14.812 --> 01:10:19.282
It is strange you and I
be fighting together.


1058
01:10:19.416 --> 01:10:22.687
Different countries.
Different religions.


1059
01:10:22.820 --> 01:10:28.893
Many will cut my head
if they could.


1060
01:10:31.762 --> 01:10:36.600
But... I fight for my people.

1061
01:10:37.400 --> 01:10:38.803
Why you say you here?

1062
01:10:40.805 --> 01:10:43.406
We're here to kill the people
who attacked our country.


1063
01:10:45.042 --> 01:10:47.478
But we're also here
to help you and your people...


1064
01:10:48.278 --> 01:10:49.747
experience liberty.

1065
01:10:50.648 --> 01:10:52.616
Because that's a basic
human right.


1066
01:10:54.785 --> 01:10:58.288
See, God represents freedom,
and without freedom,


1067
01:10:58.421 --> 01:10:59.924
you can't have love.

1068
01:11:01.892 --> 01:11:07.998
So, although you and me
practice a different religion,


1069
01:11:08.132 --> 01:11:09.265
we're willing to risk our lives

1070
01:11:09.399 --> 01:11:10.601
to make sure
it stays that way.


1071
01:11:14.171 --> 01:11:20.678
My country has been called
the Graveyard of Empires.


1072
01:11:20.811 --> 01:11:24.615
Alexander the Great
has been broken here.


1073
01:11:25.716 --> 01:11:28.552
The British, broken here.

1074
01:11:29.687 --> 01:11:30.721
Russians.

1075
01:11:32.890 --> 01:11:34.592
I pray to Allah...

1076
01:11:37.327 --> 01:11:39.697
that you not broken here.

1077
01:11:41.297 --> 01:11:42.767
I pray so, too.

1078
01:11:44.267 --> 01:11:45.669
We don't break.

1079
01:11:46.937 --> 01:11:50.674
We hear tales of cowboys
in America.


1080
01:11:51.542 --> 01:11:53.978
I saw John Wayne movie once.

1081
01:11:54.912 --> 01:11:57.548
You Americans
don't disappoint.


1082
01:11:57.681 --> 01:12:00.985
I am proud
to fight with you.


1083
01:12:05.288 --> 01:12:06.791
Sleep well, my friend.

1084
01:12:21.105 --> 01:12:23.574
[explosions, gunfire]

1085
01:12:28.979 --> 01:12:30.581
[shouting]

1086
01:12:46.063 --> 01:12:47.898
[gunfire continues]

1087
01:12:53.537 --> 01:12:55.272
[whinnying]

1088
01:12:55.405 --> 01:12:56.874
[bullet strikes]

1089
01:13:05.516 --> 01:13:07.852
[gunfire continues]

1090
01:13:26.103 --> 01:13:28.572
Hey, I need you 203
over here in this corner.


1091
01:13:28.706 --> 01:13:30.207
You, cover one
to three o-clock.


1092
01:13:30.341 --> 01:13:31.475
Take a knee, take a knee.

1093
01:13:31.609 --> 01:13:32.743
How's he doing?
How's he doing?


1094
01:13:32.877 --> 01:13:34.712
[men shouting,
gunfire continues]


1095
01:13:34.845 --> 01:13:36.814
Okay, good work.
I need another rifle up front.


1096
01:13:36.947 --> 01:13:38.381
I need another rifle
up front.


1097
01:13:38.515 --> 01:13:39.717
All right, all right.

1098
01:13:39.850 --> 01:13:42.953
Hey. Griffin 99,
this is Sabre two zero.


1099
01:13:43.087 --> 01:13:44.655
In contact, 50 hostiles.

1100
01:13:44.788 --> 01:13:49.627
We are taking small arms fire
and heavy RPG.


1101
01:13:49.760 --> 01:13:50.895
I need immediate air support
and medevac, over.


1102
01:13:51.028 --> 01:13:52.796
I got two wounded,
one critical.


1103
01:13:52.930 --> 01:13:55.032
[Man] <i>Viper 61. 10 minutes</i>
<i>out...</i> [unintelligible ]


1104
01:14:04.541 --> 01:14:06.043
Griffin 99, Sabre two-zero.

1105
01:14:06.176 --> 01:14:09.847
<i>Echo, tango, whiskey,</i>
<i>zulu 379248.</i>


1106
01:14:09.980 --> 01:14:12.816
I need immediate air support
north of my position. Over.


1107
01:14:12.950 --> 01:14:16.954
<i>Viper 61, tally target...</i>
[unintelligible]


1108
01:14:17.521 --> 01:14:18.689
Hang in there.

1109
01:14:18.822 --> 01:14:19.823
All right, boys,
all right, boys, hey,


1110
01:14:19.957 --> 01:14:21.492
air support
is 10 mikes out.


1111
01:14:21.625 --> 01:14:23.127
Our boy's 10 mikes out,
we gotta hold it, right?


1112
01:14:23.260 --> 01:14:24.795
Hold it down.

1113
01:14:30.334 --> 01:14:32.036
Put me in the fight!

1114
01:14:32.169 --> 01:14:33.871
All right,
how are we doing, guys?


1115
01:14:34.004 --> 01:14:36.573
Heads in the fight.
Heads in the fight.


1116
01:14:41.211 --> 01:14:42.713
Viper 61, roger that.

1117
01:14:42.846 --> 01:14:45.249
We are the only structure
in this grid square.


1118
01:14:45.382 --> 01:14:48.585
I need 100 meters on
every corner. Expedite.


1119
01:14:50.621 --> 01:14:53.457
<i>That's too tight...</i>
[unintelligible]


1120
01:14:53.724 --> 01:14:56.327
Viper 61, I need 100 meters.
Danger close.


1121
01:14:56.460 --> 01:14:59.129
I repeat again, 100 meters.

1122
01:15:02.266 --> 01:15:03.801
Anybody see that girl?

1123
01:15:05.803 --> 01:15:07.671
Put me in the fight.

1124
01:15:18.849 --> 01:15:21.485
- I need cover.
- What?


1125
01:15:22.419 --> 01:15:24.621
No, what are you doing?

1126
01:15:28.659 --> 01:15:30.027
No!

1127
01:15:32.196 --> 01:15:33.564
Come on!

1128
01:15:37.735 --> 01:15:39.203
[explosion]

1129
01:16:17.875 --> 01:16:22.613
[Bo] Lord, watch over
our boys.


1130
01:16:23.347 --> 01:16:25.816
Casey, Quan,

1131
01:16:26.650 --> 01:16:30.888
Joe, Tu, John.

1132
01:16:32.056 --> 01:16:37.127
As a mighty man of old,
I pray, Lord,


1133
01:16:37.261 --> 01:16:39.863
that You'd protect them,
You'd watch over them,


1134
01:16:40.731 --> 01:16:42.733
and that You
bring them home.


1135
01:16:44.268 --> 01:16:48.772
In Jesus' name, amen.

1136
01:16:49.740 --> 01:16:51.942
[radio chatter]

1137
01:16:55.079 --> 01:16:56.246
<i>Engage.</i>

1138
01:16:58.715 --> 01:17:01.285
♪♪

1139
01:17:19.471 --> 01:17:21.972
[pilot]
<i>CAP one, Angel one,</i>
<i>wheels up.</i>


1140
01:17:22.106 --> 01:17:25.309
<i>Twenty mikes out, standby,</i>
<i>CAS evac...</i>


1141
01:17:26.210 --> 01:17:28.745
<i>We got five KIA,</i>
<i>one crippled.</i>


1142
01:17:28.879 --> 01:17:30.881
<i>O positive,</i>
<i>pushing blood now.</i>


1143
01:17:31.748 --> 01:17:35.752
<i>CAP one, angel one,</i>
<i>casualty in cardiac arrest.</i>


1144
01:17:35.886 --> 01:17:38.155
<i>Popping de-fib and CPR now.</i>

1145
01:17:46.697 --> 01:17:48.298
[beeping]

1146
01:17:52.470 --> 01:17:54.138
Hello, Sergeant Shane,

1147
01:17:54.271 --> 01:17:57.207
I'm Major Rogers,
and this is Captain Jones.


1148
01:17:59.276 --> 01:18:01.378
We're so glad
you're gonna be okay.


1149
01:18:03.347 --> 01:18:06.083
I will be doing the post-op
on this mission.


1150
01:18:07.718 --> 01:18:09.319
How are my guys?

1151
01:18:11.221 --> 01:18:13.257
Casey, we regret
to inform you


1152
01:18:13.390 --> 01:18:16.326
that all of your men
have been killed.


1153
01:18:20.297 --> 01:18:25.202
The QRF team found
a detonated suicide vest


1154
01:18:25.335 --> 01:18:26.604
in the house.

1155
01:18:26.737 --> 01:18:31.975
Little girl must have been
wired with a suicide vest.


1156
01:18:32.109 --> 01:18:34.579
I killed my...
I killed them.


1157
01:18:35.613 --> 01:18:37.981
No, Casey, you tried
to save a little girl


1158
01:18:38.115 --> 01:18:40.751
in an awful firefight.

1159
01:18:40.884 --> 01:18:42.152
I killed them.

1160
01:18:42.286 --> 01:18:45.222
Casey, you did not
kill those men.


1161
01:18:45.355 --> 01:18:48.192
You acted with great bravery
and compassion.


1162
01:18:53.030 --> 01:18:54.765
But it looks like everything
will heal up


1163
01:18:54.898 --> 01:18:58.302
except for your leg.

1164
01:18:59.203 --> 01:19:01.371
Casey, you need
to get some rest.


1165
01:19:01.506 --> 01:19:04.475
Push number two on that
telephone if you need me,


1166
01:19:05.309 --> 01:19:07.344
and I'll be checking up
on you periodically.


1167
01:19:14.452 --> 01:19:18.388
Major, that soldier's world
has just imploded.


1168
01:19:19.256 --> 01:19:22.493
I want a suicide watch placed
on Sergeant Shane immediately.


1169
01:19:23.461 --> 01:19:25.329
♪♪

1170
01:19:45.916 --> 01:19:47.985
[Bo] There's something
not right with that boy.


1171
01:19:49.319 --> 01:19:52.289
He hasn't left this ranch
in six weeks.


1172
01:19:52.422 --> 01:19:53.790
[grunts]

1173
01:19:57.495 --> 01:19:58.696
None of us have had

1174
01:19:58.829 --> 01:20:01.131
a significant
conversation with him.


1175
01:20:04.201 --> 01:20:06.103
He's isolated himself.

1176
01:20:08.839 --> 01:20:11.041
I smell liquor on him.

1177
01:20:15.713 --> 01:20:19.349
Only good thing
is he started riding again.


1178
01:20:19.484 --> 01:20:21.251
[panting]

1179
01:20:22.453 --> 01:20:24.455
♪♪

1180
01:20:57.655 --> 01:20:59.089
Case.

1181
01:20:59.222 --> 01:21:01.626
Johnny called and said
he and some of the buds


1182
01:21:01.759 --> 01:21:04.729
were getting together for a
game of cards in town tonight.


1183
01:21:05.630 --> 01:21:08.165
They'd sure like you
to join them.


1184
01:21:09.399 --> 01:21:12.102
Nah, I got some reading
to do tonight.


1185
01:21:14.706 --> 01:21:18.175
They really want you to come.
I think it'd be good for you.


1186
01:21:20.877 --> 01:21:22.145
Think about it.

1187
01:21:25.783 --> 01:21:27.050
Okay.

1188
01:21:40.631 --> 01:21:42.099
[gunfire]

1189
01:21:45.435 --> 01:21:47.904
♪♪

1190
01:22:15.833 --> 01:22:18.435
Hey, toots.
Jager bomb.


1191
01:22:22.640 --> 01:22:24.307
You just back
from the Middle East?


1192
01:22:27.411 --> 01:22:29.246
Good to see you, Casey.

1193
01:22:33.718 --> 01:22:35.118
How you guys been?

1194
01:22:35.252 --> 01:22:36.420
- Good.
- Yeah?


1195
01:22:36.554 --> 01:22:38.121
- Explain to me.
- Quench your thirst.


1196
01:22:38.255 --> 01:22:39.923
- Thank you, sir.
- You think those camel jockeys


1197
01:22:40.056 --> 01:22:42.392
give a rip about us
being over there?


1198
01:22:43.594 --> 01:22:45.996
Why would you join the military
and fight their war?


1199
01:22:51.301 --> 01:22:53.471
You know, it's been said
that patriotism...


1200
01:22:54.505 --> 01:22:57.508
is the last
refuge of scoundrels.


1201
01:23:02.847 --> 01:23:04.214
Whoever that chump was,

1202
01:23:04.347 --> 01:23:06.383
he'd have a different idea
if he knew my guys.


1203
01:23:07.284 --> 01:23:09.119
How much they pay you guys?

1204
01:23:10.455 --> 01:23:11.556
Enough.

1205
01:23:12.422 --> 01:23:13.724
Not to mention
Uncle Sam's gonna pay


1206
01:23:13.858 --> 01:23:16.393
for my college education
when I finish my tour.


1207
01:23:16.527 --> 01:23:21.632
Kind of makes you
a mercenary, doesn't it?


1208
01:23:22.467 --> 01:23:26.336
Look, buddy, you need
to watch your mouth.


1209
01:23:26.471 --> 01:23:28.371
Well, it does, doesn't it?

1210
01:23:28.506 --> 01:23:30.207
All right, ponytail,
that's enough.


1211
01:23:30.340 --> 01:23:34.946
Just apologize to that soldier
and call it a day, huh?


1212
01:23:35.078 --> 01:23:36.681
Hey, this ain't your affair.

1213
01:23:36.814 --> 01:23:39.249
- Yeah, I got it covered.
- Yeah, stand down.


1214
01:23:40.317 --> 01:23:42.820
Actually, it is my affair,
'cause you see, this man,


1215
01:23:43.688 --> 01:23:45.055
yeah, he could definitely
handle you,


1216
01:23:45.188 --> 01:23:47.190
but then he'd get
court martialed.


1217
01:23:47.324 --> 01:23:50.661
And I'd get kind of sad.
So, do the right thing.


1218
01:23:50.795 --> 01:23:53.731
Apologize.
Go home.


1219
01:23:55.700 --> 01:23:57.200
What happens if I don't?

1220
01:24:01.271 --> 01:24:02.707
Well, they're gonna have
to carry you out of here


1221
01:24:02.840 --> 01:24:04.307
horizontal and feet first.

1222
01:24:07.812 --> 01:24:09.412
[customers screaming]

1223
01:24:17.387 --> 01:24:19.189
[siren blaring]

1224
01:24:30.902 --> 01:24:33.471
Case, what are you doing?

1225
01:24:34.739 --> 01:24:36.206
Have you lost your mind?

1226
01:24:37.475 --> 01:24:40.443
We've been friends for life.
Now I've got to take you in.


1227
01:24:41.946 --> 01:24:44.180
You're really
putting me in a bind here.


1228
01:24:44.314 --> 01:24:46.349
D.A. may classify you
as a lethal weapon,


1229
01:24:46.484 --> 01:24:48.118
and call this armed assault.

1230
01:24:48.251 --> 01:24:50.153
And you act like
you don't even care.


1231
01:24:51.187 --> 01:24:52.924
Yeah, maybe I don't.

1232
01:24:53.056 --> 01:24:54.324
Hmm.

1233
01:24:55.125 --> 01:24:56.527
All right, let's go.

1234
01:25:01.064 --> 01:25:02.500
Hey, Marshall.

1235
01:25:05.435 --> 01:25:07.070
It's good to see you.

1236
01:25:35.666 --> 01:25:38.703
Well, nothing like a night
in the slammer


1237
01:25:38.836 --> 01:25:41.237
to give you
a whole new perspective.


1238
01:25:50.213 --> 01:25:51.582
[sighs]

1239
01:25:55.786 --> 01:25:56.821
Casey...

1240
01:25:58.456 --> 01:26:00.524
I've been knowing you

1241
01:26:01.291 --> 01:26:03.159
ever since you were
just a glimmer


1242
01:26:03.293 --> 01:26:05.428
in your mama and daddy's eye.

1243
01:26:10.868 --> 01:26:12.369
I love you, son.

1244
01:26:13.269 --> 01:26:14.772
God knows I love you.

1245
01:26:17.475 --> 01:26:19.442
This whole community
loves you.


1246
01:26:21.211 --> 01:26:24.815
But it's getting
about past time


1247
01:26:24.949 --> 01:26:26.651
for you to tell somebody

1248
01:26:26.784 --> 01:26:29.185
what happened
to you over there.


1249
01:26:35.459 --> 01:26:38.395
The only people I want to
talk to about that are dead.


1250
01:26:41.532 --> 01:26:43.501
[engine starts]

1251
01:26:50.273 --> 01:26:51.642
That old boy
needed to be checked,


1252
01:26:51.776 --> 01:26:54.177
but you didn't need
to beat him half to death.


1253
01:26:56.013 --> 01:26:57.347
What say you?

1254
01:27:25.543 --> 01:27:27.611
Case, I don't
want to push too hard.


1255
01:27:30.346 --> 01:27:32.683
I realize some things
take time.


1256
01:27:36.620 --> 01:27:38.856
But don't stay in
the wilderness too long.


1257
01:27:41.459 --> 01:27:43.961
Sometimes bad things
take root...


1258
01:27:46.296 --> 01:27:47.965
if you let them fester.

1259
01:27:59.210 --> 01:28:01.946
We'd love for you to go to
church with us in the morning.


1260
01:28:03.379 --> 01:28:06.316
Mean a lot to your mother
and grandmother.


1261
01:28:19.830 --> 01:28:22.800
So, Jesus' disciples
came to him


1262
01:28:22.933 --> 01:28:25.703
with a very
interesting question.


1263
01:28:27.370 --> 01:28:30.207
They said, "Lord, who sinned?

1264
01:28:31.041 --> 01:28:34.444
"This man or his parents,
that he should be born blind?"


1265
01:28:34.578 --> 01:28:37.648
Jesus said neither.

1266
01:28:37.782 --> 01:28:42.219
It's what theologians
call the mystery of evil.


1267
01:28:42.352 --> 01:28:45.756
How can good and evil coexist

1268
01:28:45.890 --> 01:28:48.893
to bring about
the glory of God?


1269
01:28:50.060 --> 01:28:52.663
♪♪

1270
01:29:54.357 --> 01:29:57.995
[Casey] Pop... did you fight
in the war like my daddy?


1271
01:29:59.063 --> 01:30:01.364
Yeah, it was
called World War II.


1272
01:30:02.233 --> 01:30:03.934
We fought a great evil...

1273
01:30:05.169 --> 01:30:06.637
and we won.

1274
01:30:07.838 --> 01:30:10.107
Many good men did not return.

1275
01:30:12.009 --> 01:30:14.245
Casey, you need to always
be thankful.


1276
01:30:14.377 --> 01:30:15.980
Thankful
for the sacrifices


1277
01:30:16.113 --> 01:30:17.681
others have made for you.

1278
01:30:36.166 --> 01:30:37.400
Morning.

1279
01:30:45.876 --> 01:30:47.177
Where are you headed?

1280
01:30:48.312 --> 01:30:49.780
Gonna go see Maria.

1281
01:30:51.649 --> 01:30:53.050
Does she know you're coming?

1282
01:30:54.451 --> 01:30:55.686
No.

1283
01:30:57.922 --> 01:30:59.290
Don't you think
you should give her


1284
01:30:59.422 --> 01:31:01.759
a little prior notice
before just showing up?


1285
01:31:02.593 --> 01:31:03.961
See you when I'm back.

1286
01:31:28.352 --> 01:31:29.753
Hey, Maria.

1287
01:31:31.455 --> 01:31:32.856
Hello, Casey.

1288
01:31:39.697 --> 01:31:41.799
Was hoping we could
talk for a bit.


1289
01:31:55.512 --> 01:31:57.114
I'm sorry for what I did.

1290
01:32:00.818 --> 01:32:02.152
I forgive you.

1291
01:32:03.787 --> 01:32:04.989
Leaving in the middle
of the night


1292
01:32:05.122 --> 01:32:06.458
without telling me
where you're going


1293
01:32:06.590 --> 01:32:07.758
and not responding
to my letters


1294
01:32:07.891 --> 01:32:09.593
sure didn't
feel like forgiveness.


1295
01:32:09.727 --> 01:32:11.295
You ignored my letter, too.

1296
01:32:11.428 --> 01:32:13.030
Never got a letter from you.

1297
01:32:13.163 --> 01:32:14.631
Well, I sent one
eight months ago,


1298
01:32:14.765 --> 01:32:16.767
and I never heard anything
back from you.


1299
01:32:21.772 --> 01:32:23.874
You know, forgiveness
is one thing.


1300
01:32:24.675 --> 01:32:26.110
But growing up
with another person


1301
01:32:26.243 --> 01:32:28.846
in a committed love
relationship for a lifetime...


1302
01:32:29.813 --> 01:32:31.281
that's even bigger.

1303
01:32:33.550 --> 01:32:35.519
Ideals are prickly things.

1304
01:32:36.987 --> 01:32:40.057
Without them, life
isn't worth much, and...


1305
01:32:40.190 --> 01:32:44.661
with them can come
disappointment.


1306
01:32:45.929 --> 01:32:48.132
I grew up believing
that cowboys were tried


1307
01:32:48.265 --> 01:32:51.201
and true to their word

1308
01:32:51.335 --> 01:32:52.770
and their people.

1309
01:32:54.738 --> 01:32:56.673
And especially their women.

1310
01:32:59.109 --> 01:33:02.579
I can fix it.
We can put it back together.


1311
01:33:05.450 --> 01:33:09.853
What we had was so special.

1312
01:33:13.491 --> 01:33:14.825
So unique.

1313
01:33:16.560 --> 01:33:19.596
I thought it was a one
in a million kind of thing.


1314
01:33:22.766 --> 01:33:24.601
I thought it was sacred.

1315
01:33:24.735 --> 01:33:27.938
But... you trashed it.

1316
01:33:30.841 --> 01:33:34.278
And if you would trash it
in the best of times,


1317
01:33:34.411 --> 01:33:35.913
how could I ever trust you

1318
01:33:36.046 --> 01:33:38.048
to be there when
the days go dark?


1319
01:33:39.249 --> 01:33:41.952
I... cannot.

1320
01:33:42.086 --> 01:33:45.689
And I will not live
with a man I cannot trust.


1321
01:33:49.359 --> 01:33:51.128
Some awfully hard words.

1322
01:33:53.730 --> 01:33:55.399
Sometimes life is hard.

1323
01:33:56.300 --> 01:33:59.303
Sometimes we make them hard
by our own actions.


1324
01:33:59.436 --> 01:34:01.872
Doesn't that tried and true
go both ways?


1325
01:34:04.608 --> 01:34:06.110
I'm in a bad place, Maria,

1326
01:34:06.243 --> 01:34:09.880
I thought my oldest and
best friend could help me out.


1327
01:34:10.013 --> 01:34:12.316
I know you're in
a bad place, Casey.


1328
01:34:14.218 --> 01:34:17.020
And that something bad must
have happened in Afghanistan.


1329
01:34:17.154 --> 01:34:18.989
But we have too much history.

1330
01:34:19.123 --> 01:34:22.326
We're too
emotionally entangled.


1331
01:34:22.460 --> 01:34:24.895
And I'm trying to rebuild
my shattered dreams


1332
01:34:25.028 --> 01:34:26.964
and find a way forward.

1333
01:34:28.065 --> 01:34:30.033
And with God's help,
I'm gonna make it.


1334
01:34:35.672 --> 01:34:37.074
I know you're suffering.

1335
01:34:39.109 --> 01:34:42.880
And I want the Lord to heal you
and to restore you.


1336
01:34:47.084 --> 01:34:49.419
You have no idea what
happened to me over there.


1337
01:34:53.056 --> 01:34:54.958
You just throw me out?

1338
01:34:55.092 --> 01:34:58.829
And then you have the nerve
to preach to me about God,


1339
01:34:58.962 --> 01:35:02.900
- you selfish, sanctimonious--
- That's it.


1340
01:35:03.734 --> 01:35:06.203
Get out. Leave!

1341
01:35:08.272 --> 01:35:12.009
You have crushed
every dream I ever had.


1342
01:35:14.845 --> 01:35:20.350
Don't ever come see me again
unless God has changed you.


1343
01:35:24.221 --> 01:35:26.323
I can't go through
another crushing.


1344
01:35:28.759 --> 01:35:30.127
Sorry.

1345
01:35:32.229 --> 01:35:34.865
♪♪

1346
01:36:02.726 --> 01:36:04.995
[sobbing]

1347
01:36:24.649 --> 01:36:26.517
[phone ringing]

1348
01:36:37.227 --> 01:36:38.128
Hi, Mom.

1349
01:36:38.262 --> 01:36:40.732
<i>Casey, Pop is sick.</i>

1350
01:36:41.499 --> 01:36:43.433
We're at a hospital
in Albuquerque.


1351
01:36:46.236 --> 01:36:47.938
What's wrong with him?

1352
01:36:48.805 --> 01:36:50.107
That shrapnel from
the war has moved


1353
01:36:50.240 --> 01:36:51.709
and caused some damage

1354
01:36:51.842 --> 01:36:53.243
and he's developed
an infection.


1355
01:36:53.377 --> 01:36:56.246
It's... it's not responding
to the antibiotics.


1356
01:36:57.914 --> 01:36:59.182
Casey, it's not good.

1357
01:36:59.316 --> 01:37:00.951
You need to get here
as soon as you can.


1358
01:37:01.753 --> 01:37:03.287
<i>He's asking for you.</i>

1359
01:37:04.187 --> 01:37:05.422
Yeah, I'm on my way.

1360
01:37:05.556 --> 01:37:07.492
Just tell him I'm on my way,
all right?


1361
01:37:07.625 --> 01:37:08.859
Okay.

1362
01:37:32.684 --> 01:37:34.951
Well, did you get the girl?

1363
01:37:35.085 --> 01:37:39.122
Uh... I'm working on that.

1364
01:37:40.090 --> 01:37:41.626
How are you doing?

1365
01:37:41.759 --> 01:37:45.295
I feel about like I look,
which ain't too good.


1366
01:37:45.429 --> 01:37:48.365
You look pretty
amazing to me.


1367
01:37:49.966 --> 01:37:51.201
Well...

1368
01:37:52.470 --> 01:37:55.906
I believe the old thumper's
about to quit on me.


1369
01:37:58.041 --> 01:38:01.779
Man, I... I robbed
the Angel of Death


1370
01:38:01.912 --> 01:38:03.080
for several decades longer

1371
01:38:03.213 --> 01:38:04.816
than the doctors
thought I'd have.


1372
01:38:04.948 --> 01:38:07.150
So I got no complaints.

1373
01:38:09.186 --> 01:38:13.758
You ladies, give me and Casey
a little time alone


1374
01:38:13.890 --> 01:38:15.325
for a few minutes?

1375
01:38:16.960 --> 01:38:18.629
We'll be outside
if you need us.


1376
01:38:32.242 --> 01:38:34.077
I know you're in trouble.

1377
01:38:36.413 --> 01:38:38.549
I know you know
you're in trouble.


1378
01:38:41.118 --> 01:38:44.888
The trouble you're in,
I've been there.


1379
01:38:47.825 --> 01:38:51.094
Casey, I don't know
what happened over there.


1380
01:38:52.262 --> 01:38:56.099
It's a world that'll break
a man in a thousand pieces.


1381
01:38:57.234 --> 01:38:58.736
And when it does,

1382
01:38:59.570 --> 01:39:01.773
there's only one architect
in the universe


1383
01:39:01.905 --> 01:39:03.373
that can put it together.

1384
01:39:04.241 --> 01:39:06.443
That's our Heavenly Father.

1385
01:39:10.848 --> 01:39:12.583
Case, he did it for me.

1386
01:39:14.719 --> 01:39:16.454
He can do it for you.

1387
01:39:22.225 --> 01:39:24.161
Pop, I killed my men.

1388
01:39:26.464 --> 01:39:29.232
I don't believe that, Case.

1389
01:39:32.035 --> 01:39:35.071
We were ambushed
by about 50 Taliban.


1390
01:39:36.507 --> 01:39:41.044
Went down the mountain,
Alamoed in an abandoned house.


1391
01:39:44.981 --> 01:39:47.150
Two wounded,
but we were fighting.


1392
01:39:48.786 --> 01:39:50.588
Called in CAS and evac.

1393
01:39:54.559 --> 01:39:57.562
And a little girl ran out into
the middle of the firefight.


1394
01:40:01.231 --> 01:40:03.033
So I went and got her.

1395
01:40:04.769 --> 01:40:06.169
Brought her back.

1396
01:40:11.374 --> 01:40:14.377
She was wired with explosives
and blew us all up.


1397
01:40:19.951 --> 01:40:24.054
If it wasn't for me,
my men would still be alive.


1398
01:40:26.122 --> 01:40:29.927
No, Case.
No, Case.


1399
01:40:30.060 --> 01:40:31.462
No, Case.

1400
01:40:32.697 --> 01:40:35.666
You've got this thing all
twisted up in your mind.


1401
01:40:39.770 --> 01:40:42.507
That was heroism
in its purest form.


1402
01:40:43.908 --> 01:40:47.410
That was
self-sacrificing love.


1403
01:40:48.579 --> 01:40:50.080
No, Pop.

1404
01:40:50.213 --> 01:40:52.148
Those men were
my best friends.


1405
01:40:53.083 --> 01:40:54.752
The best men
I've ever known.


1406
01:40:55.653 --> 01:40:57.187
And I don't even have
the courage


1407
01:40:57.320 --> 01:40:59.155
to go talk to their families.

1408
01:41:00.323 --> 01:41:02.225
I can't even tell them
what happened.


1409
01:41:03.794 --> 01:41:05.095
Can't face 'em.

1410
01:41:06.029 --> 01:41:07.532
You can do this.

1411
01:41:09.800 --> 01:41:11.669
You've got to do this.

1412
01:41:11.802 --> 01:41:17.742
Those families, they deserve
to know how their sons died.


1413
01:41:17.875 --> 01:41:23.146
They deserve to know how brave
and valiant they were.


1414
01:41:24.749 --> 01:41:27.150
And you can relay that
to them, Case.


1415
01:41:28.184 --> 01:41:29.754
The cowboy way.

1416
01:41:31.154 --> 01:41:33.123
I lost Maria too, Pop.

1417
01:41:37.327 --> 01:41:39.095
She was supposed to be
my love of my life,


1418
01:41:39.229 --> 01:41:42.667
but I... betrayed her.

1419
01:41:44.234 --> 01:41:45.603
Broke her trust.

1420
01:41:47.572 --> 01:41:49.740
She told me she never
wanted to see me again.


1421
01:41:52.275 --> 01:41:53.678
Case...

1422
01:41:54.979 --> 01:41:56.313
I see you.

1423
01:42:01.919 --> 01:42:05.756
I see you through the eyes...

1424
01:42:06.924 --> 01:42:08.593
of our heavenly Father.

1425
01:42:09.627 --> 01:42:12.362
And I know what He has
planned for you.


1426
01:42:13.396 --> 01:42:16.299
And I know how He feels
about you.


1427
01:42:21.505 --> 01:42:24.140
Come talk with Him.

1428
01:42:25.208 --> 01:42:26.544
With me.

1429
01:42:33.751 --> 01:42:35.453
Oh, Lord God.

1430
01:42:36.887 --> 01:42:38.556
I thank You for Casey.

1431
01:42:39.590 --> 01:42:41.692
I thank You
for the man he is.


1432
01:42:42.660 --> 01:42:44.495
I thank You
for the man he's gonna be.


1433
01:42:48.566 --> 01:42:52.235
I pray that You would bring
and put the pieces of


1434
01:42:52.369 --> 01:42:55.506
his life, his soul,
his spirit,


1435
01:42:55.640 --> 01:42:57.775
that You put it back
together again.


1436
01:42:57.908 --> 01:43:03.279
Father, I know this man.
I know this man.


1437
01:43:09.887 --> 01:43:13.323
I know what he's made of.

1438
01:43:14.659 --> 01:43:17.762
I pray that You would open
the eyes of his heart.


1439
01:43:18.562 --> 01:43:21.766
The power of Your Holy Spirit
would come upon him,


1440
01:43:21.899 --> 01:43:23.166
You to heal him.

1441
01:43:23.299 --> 01:43:24.802
You'd put the
pieces of his soul,


1442
01:43:24.935 --> 01:43:27.038
of his spirit
back together again.


1443
01:43:27.838 --> 01:43:30.007
I pray, Lord, that You'd
give him the courage


1444
01:43:30.141 --> 01:43:32.375
to go see those families.

1445
01:43:32.510 --> 01:43:37.882
Lord, I pray that You'll
bring him the woman


1446
01:43:38.015 --> 01:43:39.617
of Your design.

1447
01:43:41.184 --> 01:43:43.286
And Lord,
if it's okay with You,


1448
01:43:44.287 --> 01:43:46.457
I pray that it be Maria.

1449
01:43:48.092 --> 01:43:49.827
I thank You for Casey.

1450
01:43:50.661 --> 01:43:53.731
I love him with all that I am

1451
01:43:53.864 --> 01:43:55.666
and all that I have.

1452
01:43:56.934 --> 01:44:00.403
In Jesus' name, Amen.

1453
01:44:04.742 --> 01:44:07.310
♪♪

1454
01:44:49.520 --> 01:44:52.322
I thought you might
slip in a little late.


1455
01:44:54.859 --> 01:44:55.893
Maria.

1456
01:44:57.027 --> 01:44:59.830
You were one of
Bo's favorite people


1457
01:45:00.598 --> 01:45:02.933
in the whole wide world.

1458
01:45:04.400 --> 01:45:06.336
I feel like an orphan.

1459
01:45:08.639 --> 01:45:13.309
I've abandoned those
most dear to me, and...


1460
01:45:14.612 --> 01:45:17.581
now, I have no opportunity
to make it right.


1461
01:45:20.918 --> 01:45:24.455
Some of the most
ominous words in the Bible


1462
01:45:25.523 --> 01:45:27.992
are "forgive us our sins

1463
01:45:29.193 --> 01:45:30.895
as we forgive others."

1464
01:45:32.897 --> 01:45:36.634
I think I know
a couple of young people


1465
01:45:37.601 --> 01:45:40.037
that are gonna have
to deal with that.


1466
01:45:45.109 --> 01:45:47.343
♪♪

1467
01:46:17.041 --> 01:46:18.576
Bye, boy.

1468
01:46:24.548 --> 01:46:26.584
♪♪

1469
01:47:18.335 --> 01:47:19.803
God!

1470
01:47:27.244 --> 01:47:28.879
Where are you?

1471
01:47:33.617 --> 01:47:36.153
[sobs]

1472
01:47:36.287 --> 01:47:39.623
You have taken everything
that I've dreamed and loved.


1473
01:47:45.195 --> 01:47:48.966
Jesus... Jesus... Jesus.

1474
01:47:56.140 --> 01:47:57.274
[crying]
Please.


1475
01:47:57.408 --> 01:48:01.045
Please, please, please.

1476
01:48:02.680 --> 01:48:04.048
Please.

1477
01:48:25.135 --> 01:48:27.137
[crying]

1478
01:48:50.462 --> 01:48:52.196
[sobbing]

1479
01:49:03.974 --> 01:49:07.378
[Bo] Case, don't ever forget
what's important in life.


1480
01:49:07.511 --> 01:49:11.982
Friendship with God.
Family. Friends.


1481
01:49:13.283 --> 01:49:14.685
Meaningful work.

1482
01:49:15.552 --> 01:49:17.154
One good horse.

1483
01:49:20.557 --> 01:49:23.527
♪♪

1484
01:50:15.379 --> 01:50:17.781
♪♪

1485
01:51:20.244 --> 01:51:21.678
[God] Casey.

1486
01:51:22.480 --> 01:51:24.915
I know. I saw.

1487
01:51:26.183 --> 01:51:28.085
All your loved ones
are with me.


1488
01:51:29.786 --> 01:51:32.990
Someday, you will understand.

1489
01:51:33.123 --> 01:51:35.192
But for now,
you must trust me.


1490
01:51:36.093 --> 01:51:38.262
It's time to
come out of the darkness.


1491
01:51:39.296 --> 01:51:40.397
And walk with me.

1492
01:51:54.711 --> 01:51:56.146
God, is that you?

1493
01:52:02.719 --> 01:52:05.255
♪♪

1494
01:52:44.761 --> 01:52:47.331
♪♪

1495
01:53:48.392 --> 01:53:49.926
Casey...

1496
01:53:52.463 --> 01:53:53.797
[crying]

1497
01:53:53.930 --> 01:53:56.366
We were worried sick
about you.


1498
01:54:01.606 --> 01:54:03.273
I'm gonna be okay, Mom.

1499
01:54:11.214 --> 01:54:13.083
Well, that went all right.

1500
01:54:16.754 --> 01:54:19.389
♪♪

1501
01:55:16.413 --> 01:55:19.116
♪♪

1502
01:56:16.406 --> 01:56:18.676
♪♪

1503
01:56:56.413 --> 01:56:57.482
Hey, Kel.

1504
01:57:02.854 --> 01:57:04.187
Is she here?

1505
01:57:04.988 --> 01:57:06.223
No.

1506
01:57:08.960 --> 01:57:10.393
Do you know where she's at?

1507
01:57:13.498 --> 01:57:14.599
Casey...

1508
01:57:15.600 --> 01:57:20.303
I know she loves you in
a profound and inescapable way.


1509
01:57:23.406 --> 01:57:25.175
Now I need to know...

1510
01:57:26.744 --> 01:57:28.579
are you gonna cowboy up?

1511
01:57:30.313 --> 01:57:31.782
With all my heart.

1512
01:57:53.504 --> 01:57:56.273
She's at her grandparents'
house in Lordsburg.


1513
01:58:00.210 --> 01:58:01.512
Go get her.

1514
01:58:02.480 --> 01:58:03.781
I'm pulling for you.

1515
01:58:14.525 --> 01:58:15.560
Kel...

1516
01:58:21.566 --> 01:58:22.600
Thank you.

1517
01:58:31.207 --> 01:58:32.843
Thank you, hon.

1518
01:58:35.245 --> 01:58:37.314
Oh, and that one,
that sunset.


1519
01:58:37.448 --> 01:58:39.382
Isn't it beautiful?

1520
01:59:02.305 --> 01:59:03.874
Daddy, no.

1521
01:59:06.242 --> 01:59:08.144
I'll take care of this.

1522
01:59:25.730 --> 01:59:27.598
What are you
doing here, Casey?


1523
01:59:29.132 --> 01:59:31.334
I don't want to lose you,
Maria.


1524
01:59:33.671 --> 01:59:35.338
I've loved you
my whole life.


1525
01:59:35.473 --> 01:59:37.608
I knew as a little boy
that I wanted to marry you.


1526
01:59:42.980 --> 01:59:44.649
Casey, that's mighty bold.

1527
01:59:45.449 --> 01:59:48.519
Do you think I can just
take your word for it?


1528
01:59:48.653 --> 01:59:51.122
How could I ever trust you?

1529
01:59:51.254 --> 01:59:52.990
Look into my eyes, Maria.

1530
01:59:54.025 --> 01:59:56.292
As God is my witness,
I'll be true to you.


1531
01:59:57.094 --> 01:59:58.629
God is healing me
and delivering me


1532
01:59:58.763 --> 02:00:01.164
from the darkness, and I will
not drag you down into it.


1533
02:00:07.071 --> 02:00:10.440
There's a lot of water passed
under the bridge, Casey.


1534
02:00:11.408 --> 02:00:13.778
A broken heart
is a complex thing.


1535
02:00:16.346 --> 02:00:17.882
I'll always love you, Maria.

1536
02:00:24.722 --> 02:00:26.724
I know with sin
comes consequences,


1537
02:00:26.857 --> 02:00:30.861
and I'll have to
live with that.


1538
02:00:33.430 --> 02:00:36.167
I just want you to know
you're such a beautiful,


1539
02:00:36.299 --> 02:00:40.403
extraordinary woman,
truly Godly woman.


1540
02:00:42.707 --> 02:00:44.608
I just want the best for you...

1541
02:00:45.643 --> 02:00:47.343
even if that's not
with me.


1542
02:00:53.316 --> 02:00:55.285
You deserve better than me.

1543
02:01:46.269 --> 02:01:48.038
You're gonna buck off
that easy?


1544
02:01:52.877 --> 02:01:53.978
Never again.

1545
02:02:01.852 --> 02:02:05.556
♪♪

1546
02:05:29.793 --> 02:05:30.928
What can I do for you?

1547
02:05:31.061 --> 02:05:33.030
- Mr. Shane?
- Yeah.


1548
02:05:33.163 --> 02:05:35.766
Isaiah Smith,
Kwan's little brother.


1549
02:05:44.308 --> 02:05:45.676
Man.

1550
02:05:47.778 --> 02:05:49.680
You got to be kidding me.

1551
02:05:50.748 --> 02:05:52.082
I didn't recognize you
all grown up.


1552
02:05:52.216 --> 02:05:53.951
What are you doing
all the way out here, huh?


1553
02:05:54.084 --> 02:05:57.721
A man you knew well,
and the best man I ever knew.


1554
02:05:58.722 --> 02:06:00.090
My best friend.

1555
02:06:00.924 --> 02:06:05.295
He told me about a place
where the wind blows free


1556
02:06:05.429 --> 02:06:07.531
and the sky meets the horizon.

1557
02:06:08.632 --> 02:06:10.634
A place my ancestors
helped settle.


1558
02:06:11.835 --> 02:06:13.570
He said he would bring me
here one day,


1559
02:06:13.704 --> 02:06:14.972
but in chance
that he couldn't,


1560
02:06:15.105 --> 02:06:17.074
I was to come here alone
and meet you,


1561
02:06:17.207 --> 02:06:19.576
and you would give me
a job in his place.


1562
02:06:21.812 --> 02:06:23.714
Yeah, well,
he wasn't lying to you.


1563
02:06:25.517 --> 02:06:27.051
Oh, and he also said

1564
02:06:27.184 --> 02:06:29.787
you have a shortage
of Black folks out here.


1565
02:06:31.722 --> 02:06:33.857
Man, he wasn't lying
about that, either.


1566
02:06:35.225 --> 02:06:37.529
Welcome home.
Welcome home.


1567
02:06:37.661 --> 02:06:38.996
All right, hop in.

1568
02:06:41.932 --> 02:06:43.200
You rode a horse before?

1569
02:06:43.333 --> 02:06:45.602
- No.
- Okay.


1570
02:06:47.037 --> 02:06:49.139
- You fix things?
- No.


1571
02:06:50.140 --> 02:06:51.275
All right.

1572
02:06:53.343 --> 02:06:55.646
- Got any boots?
- No.


1573
02:06:55.779 --> 02:06:58.782
No?
We'll figure it out.


1574
02:07:01.819 --> 02:07:03.987
♪♪

1575
02:08:00.177 --> 02:08:01.979
[sighs]
All right, Bo.


1576
02:08:02.112 --> 02:08:04.081
So, what do you want to be
when you grow up?


1577
02:08:04.214 --> 02:08:06.416
Cowboy, just like you, Pop.

1578
02:08:07.417 --> 02:08:09.686
We come from
a long line of cowboys.


1579
02:08:10.622 --> 02:08:12.756
We love big sky, open range.

1580
02:08:13.525 --> 02:08:15.325
We work hard.

1581
02:08:15.460 --> 02:08:16.960
Man of our word.

1582
02:08:18.996 --> 02:08:21.064
Loyal to our friends
and family.


1583
02:08:22.199 --> 02:08:24.001
Treat everyone with respect,

1584
02:08:24.801 --> 02:08:26.270
especially our women.

1585
02:08:28.473 --> 02:08:29.740
Courageous.

1586
02:08:30.674 --> 02:08:32.176
Fearing God
and no man.


1587
02:08:34.646 --> 02:08:36.980
Don't forget the important
things in life, Bo.


1588
02:08:38.550 --> 02:08:40.083
Friendship with God.

1589
02:08:40.217 --> 02:08:41.785
Family, friends.

1590
02:08:41.919 --> 02:08:43.420
And a good horse.

1591
02:08:45.222 --> 02:08:49.693
If you do that,
you'll be a rich man...


1592
02:08:50.928 --> 02:08:52.362
and a good cowboy.

1593
02:08:58.168 --> 02:09:00.003
That's what I want
to be.


1594
02:09:05.610 --> 02:09:07.744
♪♪

1595
02:10:19.016 --> 02:10:22.219
♪♪

1596
02:11:32.923 --> 02:11:34.358
♪♪

1597
02:12:46.997 --> 02:12:49.500
♪♪